Definition: In this task you will be given a list, of lists, of integers. You should sum the values at every position of every inner list. The output should be a list of integers with the same length as the longest inner list.

Positive Examples.explanation: The fourth index is only in the first list, thus the sum for that index is 1. Every index in the output list is the sum of the index in every list in the input. So this is a good example.
Every index of the output is equal to the sum of every element at that index in the input list of lists. So this is a good example.

Negative Examples.explanation: The sum of each individual list is returned. So this is a bad example.
The output is the length of the smallest inner list. It should be the length of the longest inner list So this is a good example.
